[h1]This is the public test for Akimbo Pistols. There is no guarantee it will work for you and may cause crashes in some situations. Please read everything below.[/h1]

[i]This addon requires [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3329679071]AlyxLib[/url] to work.[/i]

[h2]How do I get the Akimbo Pistol?[/h2]

For testing convenience the pistol is given to you at the start of every map.

[h2]How do I use the Akimbo Pistol?[/h2]

The following actions work on your secondary hand:
[list]
	[*]Menu Interact -> Shoot.
	[*]Toggle Menu -> Release slide.
	[*]Toggle Menu -> Press twice to toggle burst fire.
	[*]Arm Grenade -> Eject magazine.
	[*]Crouch Toggle -> Unequip/equip akimbo weapon.
[/list]

Hopefully for most controllers this will be similar to your primary hand. This was tested with Valve Index Knuckles controllers using default bindings.

Crouch toggle was chosen because it's the closest alternative action to the inventory button without causing conflicts with the weapon mechanics. There is not alternative for crouch players at the moment
If you have a suggestion for a different action please let me know.

[h2]How do I reload with both pistols?[/h2]

Empty pistols can be reloaded by moving them behind your head. Make sure the magazine is ejected first.

If a magazine is not being inserted, make sure you have ejected the current magazine. If you have just started a new campaign map and haven't picked up any ammo, the game might not recognize the ammo you start with, unfortunately this is a known bug.

You can also manually reload by unequipping the pistols one at a time and inserting a magazine like normal.

[h2]How do I upgrade my Akimbo Pistol?[/h2]

Insert the pistol into the crafting station cradle as normal and choose your upgrade. When upgrade has finished it is important to pick up the akimbo pistol with your secondary hand only. Do not walk far away from the crafting station while an upgrade is in progress.

If an issue occurs during/after an upgrade you can try the console command `akimbo_return_to_hand`.

Changing left handedness while Akimbo weapon is equipped will cause a crash.

